# Z Shareable Components

`app/components/Z/` holds reusable UI building blocks shared across domains (inputs, sections, modals, toolbars, pickers). Full extraction workflow: skill **shareable-components** (`.agent/skills/shareable-components/SKILL.md`).

## When to Create

- The same UI block (form section, card, toolbar, modal pattern) is used in **2+ pages or components**.
- Usages are identical in structure and differ only by bound state, flags (e.g. disabled), or handlers.
- Do NOT extract single-use, page-specific blocks into `Z/` — keep those in the page or domain folder (e.g. `Form/`).

## Placement

- Generic, cross-domain primitive → `Z/` root (e.g. `Z/CreateButton.vue`, `Z/BackButton.vue`, `Z/Quantity.vue`).
- Domain-specific input/form section → `Z/Input/<Domain>/` (e.g. `Z/Input/Product/BasicInfoSection.vue`, `Z/Input/Order/Detail/Customer.vue`).
- List/summary filter sections → `Z/Section/` (e.g. `Z/Section/Filter/OrderSumm/`).
- Modals → `Z/Modal/`, select menus → `Z/SelectMenu/`, upload areas → `Z/Dropzone/`.

## Naming

- PascalCase file named after the component; one component per file.
- Nuxt auto-import name is path-based: `Z/Input/Product/BasicInfoSection.vue` → `<ZInputProductBasicInfoSection />`. Choose folder/file names so the resulting tag reads naturally.
- Client-only components use the `.client.vue` suffix (e.g. `TextEditor.client.vue`).

## Component API

- **State**: prefer a single `state` prop holding the parent's reactive object; use `toRef(props, 'state')` inside so `v-model="state.field"` mutations flow back. The parent stays the source of truth.
- **Behaviour flags**: mode differences are boolean/enum props (e.g. `codeDisabled` for update vs create), not copies of the component.
- **Events**: side effects the parent must own (file upload, delete, submit) are typed emits (e.g. `'update:thumbnail': [files: File[]]`), never direct store writes.
- Type everything: `defineProps<{ ... }>()` / `withDefaults(...)` and tuple-syntax `defineEmits`. Export the state type (e.g. `ProductBasicInfoState`) when parents need it.
- Keep Z components presentational and generic: no page routing logic, no Pinia store access, no repository calls — pass data in via props, raise events out.

## Conventions

- Build on Nuxt UI v4 components (`UButton`, `UFormField`, `UCard`, `UModal`, ...) before custom markup; see `styling-ui-nuxt-ui.mdc`.
- Icons from `ICONS` in `~/utils/icons`; user-facing copy through i18n (`t('...')` / `$t('...')`), with defaults resolved via `computed` when a prop overrides the translation.
- When extracting, update **all** call sites to use the new component and add minimal handlers where a usage lacked one, so the shared API stays consistent.
- Verify with `npm run typecheck` and `npm run lint` after adding or changing a Z component.
